msgid ""
"m = 294 / 10.5\n"
"print(m)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/chapters/07_expressions/expressions.rst:150
msgid ""
"Here we use variables to separate the formula from the numbers. A bit easier"
" to change the values, and a bit easier to figure out the formula."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/chapters/07_expressions/expressions.rst:153
msgid ""
"m = 294\n"
"g = 10.5\n"
"m2 = m / g\n"
"print(m2)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/chapters/07_expressions/expressions.rst:160
msgid ""
"Instead of using short variable names, if we use use descriptive variable "
"names and comments the code is *very* easy to understand."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/chapters/07_expressions/expressions.rst:163
msgid ""
"# Calculate mpg using good variable names\n"
"miles_driven = 294\n"
"gallons_used = 10.5\n"
"mpg = miles_driven / gallons_used\n"
"print(mpg)"
msgstr ""
"# Calculate mpg using good variable names\n"
"miles_driven = 294\n"
"gallons_used = 10.5\n"
"mpg = miles_driven / gallons_used\n"
"print(mpg)"

#: ../../source/chapters/07_expressions/expressions.rst:171
msgid ""
"Good variable names make code *readable*. Even a non-programmer could scan "
"that code and understand what it does. Straightforward code requires less "
"effort to find problems. Therefore, take the time to name your variables "
"well."
msgstr ""

